==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corroborant
<hw>Cor*rob"o*rant</hw> <pr>(k?r-r?b"?-r<it>a</it>nt)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>corroborans</ets>, p. pr. See
<er>Corroborate</er>.]</ety> <def>Strengthening; supporting;
corroborating.</def> <au>Bacon.</au> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>Anything which gives strength or support; a tonic.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The brain, with its proper <qex>corroborants</qex>, especially
with sweet odors and with music.</q> <rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corroborate</ent>⟦br⟧
